# Cloudflare Workers + routes — avoid common agent mistakes

Skim this on every task that touches workers, env, routes, or bindings.

## Worker `env` (bindings, secrets, vars)

- **Use** the Workers virtual module: `import { env } from "cloudflare:workers";`
- **Do not** read bindings from React Router or loader/action context (e.g. `context.cloudflare.env`). That pattern is wrong here; types and runtime expect `cloudflare:workers`.

After changing `alchemy.run.ts` bindings, `apps/web/env.d.ts` (or a durable-object `env.d.ts`), or `.env.local` / `.env.production`, run `bun run typegen` from the repo root (see root `AGENTS.md`).

## Package Alchemy apps

- Add new Workers/DOs through package-local `alchemy.run.ts` files and export consumed resources through `./alchemy`.
- Root `dev`, `deploy`, and `destroy` run Turbo graphs; package scripts call `alchemy dev/deploy/destroy --app <package-id>`.
- DO providers export namespaces/workers; consumers import those resources in their own `alchemy.run.ts`.
- Put typed Hono routes on a public `readonly app` so consumers can use `honoDoFetcherWithName(env.MyDo, "name")`.
- Use explicit `DurableObjectNamespace<MyDoRpc>` / `WorkerRef<MyWorkerRpc>` types for typed RPC/Hono surfaces. Use a branded-only namespace when a heavy base class causes recursive inference.

## Route modules (`apps/web/app/routes/`)

- For each route file, export the pathname for type-safe toolkit usage, matching the URL registered in `app/routes.ts`:
  - `import { type RoutePath } from "@firtoz/router-toolkit";`
  - `export const route: RoutePath<"/your-path"> = "/your-path";`
- Required for `formAction` / `useDynamicSubmitter` flows; omitting it breaks typed submissions. See [.cursor/skills/routing/SKILL.md](.cursor/skills/routing/SKILL.md) and [.cursor/skills/form-submissions/SKILL.md](.cursor/skills/form-submissions/SKILL.md).

## Typegen and typecheck cadence

Run from the **repository root** often while building (not only at the end):

- `bun run typegen` — after `routes.ts` changes, new routes, Alchemy/env changes
- `bun run typecheck` — after substantive edits
- `bun run lint` — before considering work done

CI runs these; running locally catches the same failures early.

## Loaders and actions: `Promise<MaybeError<...>>`

Prefer **typed success/error** from [`@firtoz/maybe-error`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@firtoz/maybe-error) — import `success`, `fail`, and the `MaybeError` type directly from that package (they are **not** re-exported by `@firtoz/router-toolkit`):

- **Loaders:** `export async function loader(...): Promise<MaybeError<YourData>>` — return `success({ ... })` or `fail("...")` so `loaderData` narrows with `loaderData.success` / `loaderData.result`.
- **Actions:** use `formAction` from `@firtoz/router-toolkit` (handler already returns `Promise<MaybeError<...>>`). For non-`formAction` actions, still return `success` / `fail` the same way.

See [.cursor/skills/routing/SKILL.md](.cursor/skills/routing/SKILL.md) and [.cursor/skills/form-submissions/SKILL.md](.cursor/skills/form-submissions/SKILL.md).
